climatePledgeFriendly.details: The Forest Stewardship Council certified products support responsible forestry, helping keep forests healthy for future generations.

features: A dry baby is a happy baby, and our size 4 diapers provide the 12-hour protection that keeps those smiles coming
The absorbent core in our diaper size 4 is not bleached or processed with chemicals containing chlorine, which prevents harmful toxins from entering waterways
Our Seventh Generation Baby Diapers size 4 FreshAIR Breathable Layer helps release humidity and pulls moisture away from baby’s skin
Seventh Generation Free and Clear with 0% Lotions, or Chlorine Bleaching, and fragrance free diapers chlorine free
Seventh Generation Diapers are made using only FSC Certified, sustainably sourced plant-based pulp, which helps nurture our planet’s forests
body.description: "Give your future Wildlife Protector a clean, fresh start with Seventh Generation size 4 Diapers. Sensitive protection for a happy today, made from materials that nurture a healthy tomorrow. Our absorbent core provides the long-lasting, 12-hour protection your busy baby needs, while our fresh air Breathable Layer helps release humidity. And that’s not all. Our Free and Clear Baby Diapers size 4 are gentle on your baby’s sensitive skin with 0% fragrances, lotions, or chlorine bleaching, and use only FSC Certified, sustainably sourced wood pulp that’s gentle on our planet’s forests, helping ensure your baby grows up on a healthy planet. Wrapped in Seventh Generation’s most absorbent, most sustainable diapers chlorine free —the future looks good on your baby. We believe in a Seventh Generation. We believe that children born today and seven generations from now deserve to live on a healthier, more equitable planet. Though they’re only in diapers now, today’s children are the future planet lovers, peace advocates, change makers, ocean stewards, humanitarians, global citizens, and wildlife protectors of tomorrow. Giving them a clean start makes it easy to feel hopeful for the future. That’s why our Sensitive Protection diapers use only FSC Certified, sustainably sourced wood fluff pulp, and no chlorine bleaching, to help protect this future. Our responsibility doesn’t end with sustainable sourcing. While today’s diapers are disposable, we’re on a mission to find a zero-waste solution. And beyond developing products, Seventh Generation advocates for real change on climate justice and other issues that are important for the health of future generations. Thank you for joining us in caring today for the next seven generations."

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great diaper, keep going back to these
reviews.reviewText: I have multiple kids and I have tried many diapers. I love seventh generation because I don't need to deal with rashes and they keep everything in. For overnight I just take it up a size or two, works like a charm and doesn't smell like chemicals or baby powder or fragrance. It's a diaper it's going to smell like it's going to smell eventually. So happy Amazon sells them because they are hard to find around me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just the best!!
reviews.reviewText: I have tried all kinds of diapers, including Costco's, Sam's, Huggis, Targets brands and this is yet the best of all of these. The diaper is not bulky as many other, it does absorb super good, it keeps the smell trap, it does not form bubbles after filled by pee (like other diapers does) and it does not smells like plastics, as some brand does. And mot importantly, it does not irritate my baby skin.. Overall, the best and not reliable diaper out there.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Only diaper we’ve used for all four kids
reviews.reviewText: Been using seventh generation diapers on and off over the span of 18 years for four babies. They’ve come a long way in improving their product. My 9 month old baby has used these exclusively since birth. No diaper rash ever and very few leaks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I recently saw someone else mention little gel beads in their baby's diaper and they wanted to say that the same thing has been happening to us recently. We have NEVER had this problem and I have been using these diapers for the last 1 year with my baby. Something must have changed recently with their materials because once I started using the diaper pack we bought from Here "Amazon", I noticed the gel beads. Are these diapers defective?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I love the eco-friendliness of these diapers. They do the job and have cute prints. I wish they were a little more absorbent and had a wetness indicator. But otherwise we bought a big box and have been enjoying them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for sensitive skin!
reviews.reviewText: Only diapers that worked with our baby’s skin- she had horrible diaper rash with all the other brands. Doesn’t leak easily either- only has occasional leaks when she sleeps for over 11 hours. Diapers seem ok otherwise!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Diapers for granddaughter
reviews.reviewText: Like them because they are probably the safest for children that may have allergies

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 23, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great bang for your buck
reviews.reviewText: Pattern is adorable. Diaper covers my 16mo sons cheeks and I only need to change him 3-4x a day it holds so much and doesnt cause diaper rash.
